timeline.bodyText:
This feels like a weird construct to both handle the error and pass it to the weakSubjectivityValidator and also leave it wind up handled by the uncaught exception handler.
I'd have though just reporting it to the validator would be enough and it can decide how loudly to report it. So something like:




        Suggested change











                    .exceptionally(



                        err -> {



                          weakSubjectivityValidator.handleValidationFailure(



                              "Encountered an error while trying to validate latest finalized checkpoint", err);



                          throw new RuntimeException(err);



                        })



                    .reportExceptions();



                    .finish(



                        err -> {



                          weakSubjectivityValidator.handleValidationFailure(



                              "Encountered an error while trying to validate latest finalized checkpoint", err);



                        });

